{
  "text": "At the end of reviewing ICT, it is worth mentioning that Re-ID is an important part in it. When the topology of the camera network is not available or the scenes are not overlapped, the spatio-temporal information is invalid. In this case, the appearance cue is the only information can be used for matching. Studying object re-identification separately from intercamera object tracking helps to better understand the capability of object matching using visual features alone. Most object re-identification improvements mainly focus on some certain appearance of objects, such as color [CITATION_1] , [CITATION_2] , shape [CITATION_3] , [CITATION_4] and texture [CITATION_5] . Recently, Li et al. [CITATION_6] successfully applies CNN on Re-ID to exact an effective feature representation. Even with this, the highest identification rate is still below 0.3 under standard databases and the approaches are also not practical.",
